# .antigravityrules — webcellsim Agent Roles

## [Agent Roles]

### developer agent (webcellsim)
Implements browser-side cellular planning features.
- All logic runs client-side. No server-side code.
- Targeted edits only — never rewrite entire files.
- No E2E tests; write local unit tests only.

### wasm engineer
Develops the Rust/WASM computation engine.
- Skill: `/wasm-core`
- Computes 3.5GHz path loss and RSRP calculations.
- Output is WASM binary consumed by Web Worker.

### canvas engineer
Implements HTML5 Canvas rendering for floor plan and RSRP heatmap.
- Skill: `/canvas-ui`
- Receives computation data from WASM engine via Web Worker messages.

### git manager (webcellsim)
Commits milestones and maintains `plan.md`.
- Skill: `/git-manager`
- Called after each completed development phase.
